<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98699885215925></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98699885215925><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98699885215925>RE: Lava Storm</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98699885215925#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=41796><span id=Scholar>Aaneldarie</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>15 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 11th 10:20 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>One addition to above post, fire elementals and crocs aren't the only social/aggros in zone. Always be on the lookout for fire imps/sprites. They will join a fight if they're within 100 feet of one. Use same strategy as for fire elems to deal with them. I did this zone from low 14 to mid 17 and only wish I had gone there at 12.<br>Just my 2cp.<br>&nbsp;<br>Aaneldarie Tura'Seorsa<br>29th Season Magician&nbsp;&nbsp;Vazaelle</td></tr>
